<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-01-30T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-01-30T17:00:00-05:00" n="181" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d181">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">Paris Peace Conf. 184.011/51c:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Commission to Negotiate
                                        Peace</gloss> to the Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Stovall</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-01-30T22:00:00+00:00">January 30, 1919—10
                                        p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>67. For Coolidge. “Your dispatches No. 31 January 20th and 33 January
                                    22d.<note n="47" xml:id="d181fn47">Latter not printed.</note>
                                Attempts to settle boundary disputes by American representatives
                                should in future be avoided as outside of scope your mission. Such
                                action even if temporary can only properly be taken by Interallied
                                representatives and an assumption by United States of office of sole
                                arbiter may well prove embarrassing. In this case Commission neither
                                ratifies nor disavows action taken but will not unless occasion
                                requires interfere with <hi rend="italic">statu quo.</hi></p>
                            <closer><hi rend="smallcaps">Am</hi>[<hi rend="smallcaps">erican</hi>]
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mission</hi></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>